Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is announcing preparations for the second phase of the vaccine rollout.   JOHANNESBURG - If you're over 60, you should register for the COVID-19 vaccine. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is opening the Electronic Vaccination Data System. READ: Vaccine registration for over 60s opens as 1,372 new COVID-19 cases recorded This is in preparation for the second phase of the vaccine rollout. The country is expecting 30 million Pfizer doses, with the first batch expected to arrive in May.